('moonchildproductions-palemoon', 'Pale Moon', 'Pale Moon is an Open Source, Goanna-based web browser available for Microsoft Windows and Linux (with other operating systems in development), focusing on efficiency and ease of use. Pale Moon offers you a browsing experience in a browser completely built from its own, independently developed source that has been forked off from Firefox/Mozilla code a number of years ago, with carefully selected features and optimizations to improve the browser''s stability and user experience, while offering full customization and a growing collection of extensions and themes to make the browser truly your own.', 'Development', 'moonchildproductions-palemoon-icon', ''),
('moonlightgamestreamingproject-moonlight', 'Moonlight Game Streaming Client', 'Play games remotely from your NVIDIA GameStream-enabled PC', 'Games', 'moonlightgamestreamingproject-moonlight-icon', ''),
('moonsworth-lunarclient', 'Lunar Client', 'A modpack for all modern versions of Minecraft!', 'Utilities', 'moonsworth-lunarclient-icon', ''),
('moritzbunkus-mkvtoolnix', 'MKVToolNix', 'MKVToolNix is a set of tools to create, alter and inspect Matroska files under Linux, other Unices and Windows.', 'Utilities', 'moritzbunkus-mkvtoolnix-icon', ''),
('mozilla-firefox', 'Mozilla Firefox', 'Firefox Browser, also known as Mozilla Firefox or simply Firefox, is a free and open-source web browser developed by the Mozilla Foundation and its subsidiary, the Mozilla Corporation.
Firefox uses the Gecko layout engine to render web pages, which implements current and anticipated web standards.
In 2017, Firefox began incorporating new technology under the code name Quantum to promote parallelism and a more intuitive user interface.
Firefox is officially available for Windows 7 or newer, macOS, and Linux.
Its unofficial ports are available for various Unix and Unix-like operating systems including FreeBSD, OpenBSD, NetBSD, illumos, and Solaris Unix.', 'Development', 'mozilla-firefox-icon', ''),
('mozilla-firefox-beta', 'Mozilla Firefox (Beta)', 'Test about-to-be-released features in the most stable pre-release build of Firefox.', 'Development', 'mozilla-firefox-beta-icon', ''),
('mozilla-firefox-developeredition', 'Firefox Developer Edition', 'Firefox Developer Edition is the blazing fast browser that offers cutting edge developer tools and latest features like CSS Grid support and framework debugging.', 'Development', 'mozilla-firefox-developeredition-icon', ''),
('mozilla-firefox-esr', 'Mozilla Firefox ESR', 'Firefox ESR is the Extended-Support-Release of Mozillas webbrowser. It receives bug fixes and security updates for about 12 months, but no new functions are added.', 'Utilities', 'mozilla-firefox-esr-icon', ''),
('mozilla-firefox-nightly', 'Nightly', 'Firefox Nightly is an unstable testing and development version of Firefox.', 'Development', 'mozilla-firefox-nightly-icon', ''),
('mozilla-sops', 'Secrets OPerationS', 'sops is an editor of encrypted files that supports YAML, JSON, ENV, INI and BINARY formats and encrypts with AWS KMS, GCP KMS, Azure Key Vault, age, and PGP.', 'Design', 'mozilla-sops-icon', ''),
